result.name: Chrisly Cafe - Shau Kei Wan Shop

reviews.text: Very classic, delicious food. I love the food in this restaurant, however, I have only been here once or something...

One of the best local food place
Expect some waiting during rush hours and weekends. Just queue in front of the restaurant, and ready to tell the waiter how many people is in your group, then they will allocate you accordingly. And expect to sit closely with strangers if you r here alone or two. Yes it is crowded, but isn't that the vibe of this kind of shop? 
Scrambled egg is definitely their must-have, butter-toast too, they are thick, white and soft. Milk tea is popular too. Order 茶走 instead of original milk tea, which means condensed milk added, if you like a sweeter tea.
nice Chinese style cafe waiters are very polite try there sheung Chan "regular" meal :) and the pork chop & tomatoes with stir-fry spaghetti mhhh
Great breakfast place. Everything taste delicious!
Good service and good quality of food
